{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"64b61fee-e123-47db-bdc0-d31b8b6fced1","content":"I can point you in the right direction. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them — so it won't help here.\n\nTo analyze your `.dmp` file, use one of these tools:\n\n**`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nThen inside the REPL: `clrstack`, `pe` (print exception), `dumpheap`, etc.\n\n**`lldb` with SOS** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\n\n**WinDbg/Visual Studio** (Windows):\nOpen the `.dmp` file directly; load the SOS debugging extension.\n\n**Quick triage commands** (inside `dotnet-dump analyze`):\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n\nWould you like help setting up any of these tools in your current environment?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a0c456f8-a116-4632-91dc-0e342970e155","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":383,"requestId":"C80A:1E4705:1F3238F:22841B1:6A052B60"},"id":"cb272e8e-599c-4d6d-bb96-0b0720bb1145","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:54:50.763Z","parentId":"990fe4e3-814b-4139-b7ce-4b8381f336dc"}
